cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the robustness of deep neural networks in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new loss function for adversarial learning and a Bayesian framework for feature pruning, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of adversarial vulnerability, which is a security concern and falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a method for reducing vulnerability by suppressing features, which is related to neural network pruning (cs.NE).
